
[1]waterfall

   WATERFALL, n. [water and fall.] A fall or perpendicular descent of the
   water of a river or stream, or a descent nearly perpendicular; a
   cascade; a cataract. But the word is generally used of the fall of a
   small river or rivulet. It is particularly used to express a cascade in
   a garden, or an artificial descent of water, designed as an ornament.
